dialogue: *singing* Last King Christmas last arrived!
*singing* In the Christmas Christmas! *stops singing and smells the ham* Mmm... Jerry, you are really giving it to this ham.
Um, Merry Christmas? *puts his hands on his hips* Helloooo? My parents are coming over for the first time in years! Can we stow the gadgets and look alive?
Alive? For your parents?
Good one.
Hey man!
You ?hey man?! This holiday is about humanity.
*not looking up from his tablet* You know, I thought it was about being born half-God or something.
Okay, whatever. All electronic items are going in the stocking. Now.
*hands over his tablet* Ohhhh...
Dad, I'm not giving you my phone.
Put it in the stocking, Summer, or I'm joining Facebook.
*offscreen* Ho ho ho, everybody.
More like whoa whoa whoa. What is this? My parents are coming!
Calm down Jerry, this is Ruben, an old friend.
Pearl Harbor.
I check in on him once a year and give him a little *burp* medical *burp* evaluation.
Aw, Dad... That is so sweet.
*squinting suspiciously* Yeah, it is... I don't get it.
Korea.
Don't worry about your C-C-Christmas, Jerry. *leads Ruben away* Ruben and I'll be in my workshop while you have another day in Phil Collins? proverbial paradise.
Huh. You think you know a guy.  Okay, there's my parents. Now remember, no TV, no phones, no laptops, we are connecting this Christmas, like old-school Jews on a Saturday. *opens the door* Hey hey!
Merry Christmas, son.
Oh, hi. Can I help you?
Jerry, this is Jacob. *takes Jacob by the arm* Didn't you get our text message?
No.
You must be Jerry! That's a fine lookin? apron. William Sonoma?
*smiling uncomfortably* I wish... But thank you. *closes the door* So... you're a...friend of the family...?
*puts an arm around Jacob's shoulders* The way we see it, he's a part of the family.
Wow!

After your father's brush with cancer and losing your uncle, we looked at life and wondered how have we spent it? And how do we spend the rest of it? What are we going to be when we die? A list of fears and questions, or a collection of real experiences?
Holy crap, Joyce. That's amazing.
Then Jacob came into our lives. We're learning to live again.
All three of us.
...Cool... Eggnog?
Now we are talkin?! This man's got the apron and the eggnog, huh?
Hi Joyce, Leonard. *looks at Jacob* Hello there.
Merry Christmas, man.
Morty! A moment of your time?
He's in bad shape, Morty.
Aw geez, Rick! What did you do?
Gee, thanks Morty. What kind of monster do you think I am? I-I'm sittin? here trying to save the guy's life!  I want you to find Dr. Xenon Bloom. He'll know what's goin? on.
*extremely nervous* Uh... W-W-Where do I find Dr. Bloom?
In Ruben. *shoves a glass oxygen mask onto Morty's head*
Ruben... Minnesota?

Ruben on the table, Morty! *hooks up the backpack to the helmet* Look, I-I don't have time for you to wrap your little walnut around everything. *pulls a shrink ray into view and plugs it in* Hold your breath until the process is over or your lungs will collapse.
W-What proc?
Hey Dad, where's Morty?
He's busy.
Morty, can you hear me? Head North!
Rick... Where am I?
*adjusts his own headset as he stands in the garage* Depending on my aim, you should be just south of the entrance.
The entrance to what?
Welcome, Morty.  Welcome...  ...to Anatomy Park!
It's a little business venture I've been cookin? up on the side with Dr. Bloom.  An amusement park inside a human body. Science isn't cheap, Morty. This should really help put a dent in the overhead.
Oh my God! This is insane! Spleen Mountain? Bladder Falls? Pirates of the Pancreas?
You got a problem with that last one, Morty?
Huh? No, no, I'm just reading them out loud in the order I'm seeing them.
Okay, alright, if I sounded a little defensive, it's because Pirates of the Pancreas was my baby.
I-I got a lot of push-back when I pitched it, Morty. I guess I'm still a little defensive. Let's just find Dr. Bloom, alright? I-I'm picking up a distress signal in the liver, Morty.
Proceed to the liver.
Arriving at ?Liver?.
*stumbles forward and hits his helmet on the window* Ow!
Mind the gap.
It's really scary in here, Rick.
Liver's under maintenance. Ruben's seen some rough years, Morty. Don't judge. You don't agree to have a theme park built inside you if your life's going great.
OOOOHHH! Rick, it's a monster!
No no, Morty. The only monster here is alco? *belch* ?holism.  That is an animatronic werewolf.
Who are you? Answer me! Where did you come from?
Mmm! M-M-My-my-my Grandpa Rick sent me!
Poncho! That's quite enough.
Morty, that's Poncho.  This is Roger and Annie.
*staring sheepishly at Annie* Oh...
And I am Dr. Xenon Bloom.
Hey Bloom, it's Rick. What the hell's goin? on here?
I don't know why, but the entire security system has shut down. And I'm afraid the exhibits are unlocked.
Exhibits?
Anatomy Park's greatest attraction, young man, isn't the music or the food or the Pirates of the Pancreas.
Watch it.
It is first and foremost a living museum of humanity's most noble and ferocious diseases.
Diseases?!
Hey Doc, I have news for ya.  Your living museum is officially a wild safari!
Hepatitis A! Run!
Oh... *leans over and wipes some food from Joyce's mouth with a napkin* The food goes in your mouth, girl!
Aha... I'm sorry Jacob, I guess I'm still confused about the precise nature and origin of your relationship with my parents. Are you like a?Are you like their caretaker? Is that what it is?
We can go into detail later, son.

Now wait, there, there's no point to secrecy. Let's all live and die honestly. Your mother and I have shared forty years of each other, mind, body, and soul.  And when minds and souls are joined for eternity, and when eternity is at the door, it's an invitation to let go of the body, and an opportunity to share and experiment.
Dad, please, what are you saying?
Whatever it is, it's beautiful, Leonard. *glares at Jerry* And we support you.
Speak for yourself! Because it, heheh, it sounds like you're about to say Jacob is your lover.
No no no no.  Jacob is your mother's lover.  I watch them. Sometimes from a chair, sometimes from a closet. Almost always dressed as Superman.
Oh... *reaches across the table and puts a hand atop theirs*
Jerry, this ham's got to be all you, right? It's in-cred-i-ble.
*smirks* Happy human holiday, Dad.
AHHHHHH!
Hepatitis won't follow us into the respiratory system!
That's strange... *taps the meter* Air flow is down twenty percent.
So the brain isn't getting enough oxygen. That's why security is offline.
W-Well, I guess we better check it out.
Hey, wait for me! *removes the head of his costume*
*points his cane at Alexander* Put that back on!
If we got up to the bronchial catwalk, we could look for blockage.
*raises his hand* I'll go. *glances at Annie* Heheh...
Don't be a hero, kid.
I'm not. I'm doin? it because it's fun. *he hops from frond to frond*
*cocks his gun* We shouldn't be here.
Whatever you do, don't fire that thing in here! We must save Ruben. This is my life's work.
Ah!

It's alright, my dear. Nearly all human lungs contain a strain of this bacteria, but the scar tissue... *prods it with his cane, seeing something has escaped from the scar tissue* ...keeps them dormant. *looks up toward Morty, who is getting close to the catwalk* Morty! Get down!
Whoa! *grabs hold of the catwalk as a fluid drips down onto it* Whoa!
Oh! What are those things?!
Tuberculosis, coming in fast!
*raises gun and starts shooting at the disease* Not faster than a bullet! Ahh!
*grabs Poncho's arm* No! Do you know what you've done?!
Get to the digestive tract! He's coughing!
Waaaah! Don't let me die!
Just take a deep breath, Ruben.
You're not gonna die! What's your name?
My name is... *his hand slips from Morty's and he's coughed up* ALEXANDEEEEEEEER!
Rick! Ruben's got tuberculosis!
Oh, great work, Morty. *pulls a massive syringe form his lab coat* I'll just cure it, and then?
Okay. Well I can't cure death. This is bad, Morty. You're trapped in a dead man. Listen, if the situation keeps darkening, do yourself a favor?
?and hop by Pirates of the Pancreas. Obviously I'm biased, but, I think it's great, Morty.

*sitting in a lounge chair, pulls out a flask* It's a bunch of pirates runnin? around a-a-a- pancreas. We don't whitewash it either, Morty. The pirates are really rapey. The top priority is to get you guys out of there, but I'm just saying, if that becomes impossible?
?please, you gotta treat yourself.
Geez, what's that horrible smell?
You mean the Panda Express? *chuckles* Kidding, I-I'm kidding.  The body is beginning to constrict and fill with gas. We're inside a corpse, my boy. Anatomy Park is doomed.
Forget about the park, Doctor! How do we get out?!
The digestive tract is the evacuation route. Get it? There's an emergency station in the colon with a ray that can enlarge us all.
Everybody! Get to the colon!
Now I'm takin? orders from a twelve-year-old boy?!
Morty. The scar sacs containing the tuberculosis were sabotaged. This disaster was an inside job. Keep your eyes on Annie. She was written up several times by her manager at the churro stand.
Intestines are ahead to the left. Then the right. Then left. Et cetera.
Hey, just so you know, I-I'm actually fourteen. So, you know...
What?
Not twelve.
Okay.
Because he just said I was twelve.
Oh. Good for you.
Oh. Oh, Morty. Strike one.
*slumps forward* Nnn...
*singing* It's a road of laughter, a trail of food. It's a pathway that breaks up the fat in food. It's a tube in the chest and it sends out the rest. It's a small, small intestine!
It goes on like this for miles...
*excitedly* And then we get to the large intestine!
Shh. *shines flashlight* I hear something.
*whispers* Don't move. Gonorrhea can't see us if we don't move.
Wait! I was wrong! I was thinking of a T-rex.
We're sitting ducks!
Doc! Didn't you say the body was filling up with gas?
Yes. Why?
Kid! You're a genius! *pulls out a match*
Are you mad?!
*grabs Annie's hand* Everybody! In here!
Hey Gonorrhea! How's this for a burning sensation?
*singing* Drummer, drum, drum, drum! Drummer, drum, drum drum drum, Christmas drums!
Oh, Summer. Sing it! Haha.
Christmas drums being played by a boy!
Jerry, come on. This is what you wanted.
I get it, Beth. Be careful what you wish for. I'm being punished for taking your iPad.
What? Jerry, let that stuff go, okay? I'm sorry I was a bitch earlier. Let's just be here.
Ugh... Summer!
*stands up* Ethan, what are you doing here?
I've been texting you for hours. What the hell?!
I don't have my phone! I'm doing a human holiday!
Did you even consider how that might make me feel?
How you feel? Why is everything always happening to you?!
*stands up* Summer, do you have a boyfriend?
Yeah, do you, Summer?
I don't know Ethan, do I?
*stands up and puts a hand on Ethan and Summer's shoulders* Jerry, no disrespect, but you really need to connect more with your family, man.

I should be able to access the backup generator to get the growth ray back online. If it works, we'll be regular-sized in a few minutes. I just hope Ruben's not in a room with white carpets or upholstery.
What the hell is that?
The sphincter dam. We built it when Ruben became incontinent, but it was not designed to hold a corpse-load.
Almost got it. Everybody, move inside the circle!
Poncho? What is this in your backpack?
That's bubonic plague! What are you doing with that, Poncho?
Everybody get back!
Poncho, you son of a bitch! You released the tuberculosis so you could steal from me?

*laughs* That's right, baby. A lot of people would pay top dollar to decimate the population. I'll take the highest bidder. Al Quaeda. North Korea. Republicans! Shriners! Balding men that work out! People on the Internet that are only turned on by cartoons of Japanese teenagers! Anything is better than working for you! *points the knife at Dr. Bloom* You pompous, negligent, iTunes Gift Card as a holiday bonus-giving?
AHHHHH!!!
Ah! Eh! Get! Get off! *he backs up and falls over the railing* Ahhhh!
You guys!
It's gonna burst! *urges the others on* Go! Go, go, go! *pulls a lever before trying to run after the others but catches his foot in some of the machinery* My foot is stuck!
No!
This is okay! It's okay, just go! Tell my family I love them! They may be hard to find because my wife kept her last name and she made the kids take it too, so, I dunno, you could goo?
No!
Let me ask you something Ethan. Where's the anger coming from, man?
From Summer being a total bitch!
Where's the anger coming from?

...My brother... took me fishing once...in the bushes... *voice begins choking up as tears fill his eyes* I can't... I can't! *covers his eyes as he starts to cry* He made me feel like a girl! *sobbing openly* I'm... m-made me a girl!
He didn't make you anything, man. You are who you are. *gestures to Summer* She is who she is.  Now you go to her. Brand new.
Come here right now!
Oh my god, I'm so sorry Ethan! *they hug* I love you!
I love you so much.
Um...
You did it again, cubby. Come here.
No! Stop! I hate this!
Well, Christmas doesn't revolve around what you hate, son.
Well then, I hate Christmas! Enjoy being human! You guys are gross and lame.
My name's Ruben Ridley. You're inside me right now, but by the end of this journey, I'll be inside all of you.
My story begins in the dot com crash in the early ?90s.
*whispering to Morty* You can put your fingers wherever you want?
Morty, you wanna put it on mute or something?
I'm trying to concentrate.
Ah, Rick?
*holds up a hand without even looking over at him* Not now, Jerry. I've got much, much smaller fish to fry.
*enters anyway* I wanted to say I'm sorry I ever judged you. *leans on the ping pong table, looking down at Ruben's corpse* Right now, you're my sanest relative.
Relative? That's it! Relative size! Jerry, hand me a scalpel and a bundle of dynamite! *into his headset* Morty! Can you get to the left nipple?
Are you kidding? I'm hoping I can get to both of them, Rick.
Morty, I'm talkin? about Ruben's left nipple!
We need to get to the left nipple!

The body is decaying!  The arterial transit system is useless! We can try the service shuttle. It's connected to the skeletal system. That's why we call it the Bone Train. *to Annie* Would you like to ride the Bone Train, miss?
If it'll get us out of here.
How about you, Morty? Would you like to ride the Bone Train?
Why are you doing this bit? We're gonna die. Let's go.
Well, I can see that you're busy... Merry Christmas, Rick.
There's no autopilot. One of us will have to stay here and operate it manually.
...Uh, well...
No, you're right. It was a dick move for me to even pause like that. This is all my fault. You go on.
*points* What the hell is that?
E. coli outbreak. Hurry!
Oh wait, there is an autopilot.  WAAAIT! ...OKAY, NEVER MIND, I WANTED TO SACRIFICE MYSELF ANYWAAAAAYYYY!
They're chewing through the doors!
Euuuugh! *grabs a fire extinguisher and beats the E. coli off the train with it* We're in the areola, Rick! Almost to the nipple! But we're also in a really bad situation!
I'm almost there, Morty!
Reports are coming in from across the country about what appears to be a giant naked man over the continental United States. We now go to Tom Randolph in New York. Tom?
Well, his eyes aren't twinkling, and his dimples aren't merry, but I'm standing under a nose like a seventy-mile cherry!
Thank you, Tom. Let's go now to Eric McMan in Los Angeles.
We've got feet here on the West Coast, Bill! Giant feet, even relative to the giant man's size! And you know what they say about that!
Well, if the old adage is true, one can only wonder what is going down in the Rocky Mountains.
Oh my god, the track!
It's Hepatitis A!
The nipple hole...
It's beautiful...
Aw no!
Whoa! It's Hepatitis C!
Um... We... Did we have some sort of relationship with him?
I... think they're just like that? I think they're just good guys.
Oh. Huh.
Where's Dr. Bloom?
Sorry Rick... He's dead...
Goddamn it, Morty, I ask you to do one thing!
Jerry doesn't know what he's missing.
He'll come around, Beth. Christmas is a special time. It has funny ways of bringing families together.
I dunno, Jacob. Jerry got an invitation to be alive today, and he rejected it. I don't know if our marriage will?
It's raining blood!
Oh, shit. find Jerry!
Oh god.
Jerry!
*stands and hugs her* It's alright! The TV says there's nothing to worry about.
The giant naked sky Santa has exploded. Blood and chunks of viscera are raining down on the country. Everything should be fine.
Dad, can I have my phone back?
Sure, sweetie. *pulls out the stocking and gives Summer her phone, then gives Beth her tablet* Everybody, take a device. It'll help you relax.
This is nice.
Yeah. *puts an arm around Beth and Jacob* I guess we really learned something this Christmas, Jacob.
No we didn't, Dad. No we didn't.
Too bad about Dr. Bloom. *Rick, Annie, and Morty exit the car* He was a genius. The only man capable of creating a new Anatomy Park.
Actually, I studied Dr. Bloom's work. I believe I have the knowledge necessary to create a new, much safer park!
What about Pirates of the Pancreas...?
I think it was one of the most underrated attractions.
Booyah! Hold your breath!
Hey, wh-wh- What the hell, Rick? What the hell, man? I liked her! I really had somethin? going there, Rick!
Yeah, so I heard. You dodged a bullet, Morty, trust me. *whispers* Puffy vagina.
W-What's wrong with that? That doesn't sound like a problem to me! I dunno!
C'mon. Let's get some stuffing, I'm starving.

Oh, unbelievable. We got a bunch of robot computer people sittin? around with their faces stuffed in computer screens.  Do you realize Christ was born today? Jesus Christ our Savior was born today! A-A-A-Are you people even human? What kind of Christmas is this?
Hey Rick! Rick, can you hear me?
Loud and clear, Annie.
Great! We're also on with Alejandro, our Chief Imaginarian?
Hey Rick.
Natalie Jacobs and Chris Desiter from Microscopic Marketing, Zach from Organ Concepts and Jamie from New Media.
Hey everybody.
Hey, hi Rick, how's it goin?.
So. Pirates of the Pancreas.
Yeah, talk to me.

Hey Rick, it's Alejandro speaking. Um, so we asked ourselves internally, we asked ourselves over here, ?Okay, what does a pancreas do??  And the answer was, does it make pirates? No. It makes insulin, you know? So we're starting with a new?
So those guys are inside me, huh? Like, building a park?
Those guys are inside you building a piece of shit, Ethan! They're inside you building a monument to compromise! Fuck 'em. Fuck those people. Fuck this whole thing, Ethan.
... Cool. And who pays me?

dialogue: Leave my  Morty out of this!

dialogue: Will you at least unfreeze my daughter's idiot?

dialogue: -give you anything! I have a rare antique coin collection, just don't hurt me!  Okay, maybe not antique, but it was a limited minting. They have little R2D2s instead of George Washingtons.

dialogue: Our son's been abducted!

dialogue: You hate me for buying those coins!

dialogue: Geez, Rick! Wh-what is this place?

episode: Close Rick-Counters of the Rick Kind
dialogue: The Citadel of Ricks. It's the secret headquarters for the council of Ricks.

episode: Close Rick-Counters of the Rick Kind
dialogue: Council of Ricks?

episode: Close Rick-Counters of the Rick Kind
dialogue: As you know, Morty, I've got a lotta enemies in the universe that consider my genius a threat. Galactic terrorists, a few sub-galactic dictators, most of the entire intergalactic government: wh-wherever you find people with heads up their asses someone wants a piece of your grandpa. And a lot of versions of me on different timelines had the same problem. So a few thousand versions of me had the INGENIOUS IDEA OF BANDING TOGETHER like a herd of cattle or a school of fish or those people who answer questions on Yahoo! Answers.

dialogue: Hey, what do you know? It's a cowboy version of me!

dialogue: Geez, you're easy to impress. Yeah, most timelines have a Rick and most Ricks have a Morty. This place is a real who's-who of who's you and me.

dialogue: Fuck you?! No no no no no, fuck me!

dialogue: Bring up the holograms!

episode: Close Rick-Counters of the Rick Kind
dialogue: Twenty-seven Ricks brutally murdered in their own timelines. An unprecedented Rick-icidal epidemic. What say you, Earth Rick C-137?

episode: Close Rick-Counters of the Rick Kind
dialogue: You think I did this? Why am I the first Rick you pull in every time a Rick stubs his toe?

episode: Close Rick-Counters of the Rick Kind
dialogue: You  have a history of non-cooperation with the council.

episode: Close Rick-Counters of the Rick Kind
dialogue: Yeah, so does the scientist formerly known as Rick! Wh-wh-wh-why isn't he here in handcuffs?

episode: Close Rick-Counters of the Rick Kind
dialogue: Because he's dead too!

episode: Close Rick-Counters of the Rick Kind
dialogue: No!

episode: Close Rick-Counters of the Rick Kind
dialogue: Who else would you have us question? You fit the profile! Of all the Ricks in the Central Finite Curve, you're the Malcontent! The rogue.

episode: Close Rick-Counters of the Rick Kind
dialogue: I'm the Rick! And so were the rest of you before you formed this stupid alliance. You wanted to be safe from the government so you became a stupid government. That makes every Rick here less Rick than me.

episode: Close Rick-Counters of the Rick Kind
dialogue: Yeah, murmur it up, d-bags. Now if you'll excuse me, I've got pancakes back home with syrup on top of them. They're about to hit that critical point of syrup absorption that turns the cakes into a gross paste. And I hate to get all Andy Rooney about it, but I think we all like fluffy discs of cake with syrup on top! And I think we also like to be accused of crimes when there's evidence! So as they say in Canada, peace oot!

episode: Close Rick-Counters of the Rick Kind
dialogue: Evidence? Good idea. Scan his Portal Gun!

episode: Close Rick-Counters of the Rick Kind
dialogue: Oh, come on. Don't look at another man's Portal Gun history. We-we all go to weird places.

dialogue: Yes, but it appears you alone have been going to the exact timelines and locations in which the murders occured!

episode: Close Rick-Counters of the Rick Kind
dialogue: What? That's Rick-diculous. I'm obviously being set up!

dialogue: I've heard enough.

dialogue: Run, Morty!

dialogue: Uh uh, not you!

I'm okay... I'm okay... I'm...  Ohh...

"The Creepy Morty". What is it your kind's always saying? "Don't think about it." Come on. There's someone important I want you to meet.

After you.

SLI-I-I-I-I-I-I-ICK!!!!

You asshole! I vouched for you! He only came here because I asked him to. I'm sorry, Rick.

Pfft, you sell-out Mortys kill me. I'd hate you more than the Ricks you worship if there was any point. But you can't help it; you were bred for it. Wanna see?
You already know rogue Ricks used Morties to hide themselves from the Citadel. But you might not know it worked so well that the Citadel became its own Morty market.

And I'm sure you don't know how far they've gone to help supply meet demand. Sure, Ricks could scour infinity for naturally-occurring grandsons, but why bother? So much work. Such an admission of need.

There aren't infinite versions of our grandfather, Morty. He's an infinite smear of one shitty old man, and he's attached to us infinitely through his weakness and our forgiveness. This is why we're with him. This is why we're alive.

It isn't the whole truth.

They literally all say that. They all have that excuse; it's part of their system. None of them have to be responsible, they're all victims of themselves.  "Oh, it's so hard to be a genius!" Couldn't you just die?
Well what are you doin' about it?

Jack shit. I'm leaving. Do you know what the Central Finite Curve is? They built a wall around Infinity, separated all the infinite universes from all the infinite universes where he's the smartest man in the universe. And I'm leaving it. That's what makes me evil', being sick of him. If you've ever been sick of him, you've been evil too.

Rerouted. Rerouted. Rerouted.

Thanks, pal. I-I'm glad you ignored my advice.
It's just as well. I lied. That second seat's a toilet.
Oh, super dick move! But weirdly kind of cool to admit it.
Geez, you guys really are bred for forgiveness. Let's go.
Say goodbye to the Citadel, fellas.

Woo-wee! Evil Morty! That was quite a scheme. Makes me wonder if there's an evil me out there. But I guess, sometimes I look at my life, and I may not even need im. Cause, well, guess I made a pretty big mess of things myself. Ooo-eee.
